strings: <voice_0x010008F2><se_def>*: Haven't you had enough, Mr. Kalderasha, sir?

<voice_0x010008F3><se_def>*: I'm sorry but I've got a business to run.
This, er, haphazard fortune-telling of yours
is costing me a fortune in free drinks!

<voice_0x010008F4><se_low>Kalderasha: WHAT!? My fortune-telling... HAPHAZARD!?
Are you a complete fool!?

<voice_0x010008F5><se_low>Kalderasha: Let me tell you something for free.
All fortune-telling is ‘haphazard’!
What do you expect!?

<voice_0x010008F6><se_low>Kalderasha: Anyway, so what if I saw it?
So what if I foretold the fire?
If I'd tried to stop it, then what!?

<voice_0x010008F7><se_low>Kalderasha: It would only have led to another disaster,
that's what!

<voice_0x010008F8><se_def>*: I'm sorry, Mr. Kalderasha, sir.
I don't follow...
<voice_0x010008F9><se_def>*: If you're saying you knew about the fire, shouldn't you at least have warned Master Rylus?

<voice_0x010008FA><se_low>Kalderasha: Yes... Poor Rylus...
How many times I argued with the old man...
I cannot believe he is gone...

<voice_0x010008FC><se_low>Kalderasha: Hmm!? ...You!
Come, show your face to the Great Kalderasha!
Yes! Yeeesss!

<voice_0x010008FD><se_def>*: Q-Quick, quick!
Everyone come quick!
There's a monster in town!

<voice_0x010008FF><se_def>*: Just come and see!
The whole town's gone crazy!
